    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.31.9-10_0001" />
                <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                <note type="curatorial">Aly Collection
                122-2</note>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                <hi rend="caps">UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI</hi>
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA</hi>
                    <lb/>
                
                
                
                <hi rend="caps">COLLEGE OF ARTS AND SCIENCE</hi>
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">DEPARTMENT OF ENGLISH</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>1-10-'61</dateline>	
                
                
                
                <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>My god! You should have seen what they did to me last Sunday evening! It was a glittering wow! The enclosed pretty well suggest the story, but print can't convey the  <hi rend="underline">feel</hi> of good will, happiness, and <hi rend="underline">affection</hi> that filled the place.</p>
              
                <p>Your letter (yours &amp; Bower's) was read to the company along with the others. There was an article in the Chicago Tribune &amp; it brought letters
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.31.9-10_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">10</fw>
                    
                    from friends I've not heard from in years.</p>
                
                <p>One does not "deserve" the best things that happen in this life. They just come &amp; are to be accepted happily &amp; humbly.</p>
               
                <p>The same old love to each of you there. Your letter was <hi rend="underline">dear</hi>.</p> 
                <closer>
                <signed>John</signed> 
                </closer>
                
                <postscript><p>I'm eager to hear about the program. How I wish I could hear it!</p></postscript>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
